---
title: Meatloaf Parm over Spaghetti Marinara
description: Chicken Parm, Veal Parm, Meatball Parm… Pork Meatloaf Parm? Yes, dreams really do come true. Our chefs have Parm-ified individual pork meatloaves, layering them with mouthwatering marinara sauce and a cheesy panko topping. They’re baked until the meat is perfectly tender and the crust is crispy and melty, then served over spaghetti marinara with a sprinkle of more cheese for good measure. Parm-fection? We think so.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/62041236022fb932066bb720-2d90b2c3.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/meatloaf-parm-62041236022fb932066bb720-c81c61af.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/meatloaf-parm-62041236022fb932066bb720
servings: 2
author: Michelle Doll Olson
time required: 35 minutes
cuisine: Italian
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 1060 kcal
  fat: 51 g
  saturated fat: 20 g
  carbohydrates: 98 g
  sugar: 18 g
  protein: 51 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 1550 mg
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Bring a large #pot{}
of salted water to a boil.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup},
@mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup}, and a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoons};
season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

In a #large bowl{}, combine @ground beef{10%ounce}, half the panko mixture,
half the @Tuscan Heat Spice{1%tablespoon}, and 1 TBSP water
(2 TBSP for 4 servings); season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Form pork mixture into two 1-inch-tall loaves (four loaves for 4); flatten tops.
Place on a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}.

> Swap in beef for pork.

Evenly spread tops of meatloaves with 1 TBSP @marinara sauce{14%ounce cup} each
(you'll use the rest later). Mound with remaining panko mixture, pressing
gently to adhere.

Bake meatloaves on top rack until pork is cooked through and crust is
browned and crispy, ~{22-28%minutes}.

Once water is boiling, add @spaghetti{6%ounce} to #pot{}. Cook, stirring occasionally,
until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}.

Reserve 1/4 cup pasta cooking water (1/3 cup for 4 servings), then drain.

Heat pot used for pasta over medium-high heat. Add remaining marinara sauce,
remaining Tuscan Heat Spice, @sugar{1%teaspoon}, and reserved pasta cooking water.
Bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer. Cook until slightly thickened,
~{3-5%minutes}.

Stir drained spaghetti, half the @Parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}, and
@butter{1%tablespoon} into pot with sauce. Season generously with @salt{}
and @pepper{}.

Divide pasta between plates and top with meatloaves. Sprinkle with remaining
Parmesan and serve.

> TIP: If you prefer, serve meatloaves on the side instead.